Abdomen brown. Length: 3.33. Pygophore (
Figs. 26–27
): anterior margin of dorsal aperture slightly concave; inner projections with anterior spine, projected posteriorly. In lateral view: dorsal margin not declivent. Parameres (
Figs. 28–29
): blade gradually narrowing to apex, slightly curved; shank with a setose inner projection, with setae on upper margin and on basal portion of blade, and with external projection with four long setae. Aedeagus as in figure 30.
